            <head>“In Memory Of Colonel Charles Young”</head>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">Along the shore the tall, thin grass</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">That fringes that dark river,</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">While sinuously soft feet pass,</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">Begins to bleed and quiver.</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">The great dark voice breaks with a sob</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">Across the womb of night;</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">Above your grave the tom-toms throb,</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">And the hills are weird with light.</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">The great dark heart is like a well</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">Drained bitter by the sky,</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">And all the honeyed lies they tell</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">Come there to thirst and die.</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">No lie is strong enough to kill</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">The roots that work below;</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">From your rich dust and slaughtered will</l>
            <l enjamb="no" part="N">A tree with tongues will grow.</l>
            <byline>Countée Cullen</byline>
         </div>
      </body>
